function min_minutes(garbage, travel) {
    let time_garbage = [0, 0, 0];
    let time_travel = [0, 0, 0];

    for (let i = 0; i < garbage.length; i++) {
        let m = 0, p = 0, g = 0;
        for (let c of garbage[i]) {
            if (c === 'M') m++;
            else if (c === 'P') p++;
            else g++;
        }
        time_garbage[0] += m;
        time_garbage[1] += p;
        time_garbage[2] += g;
        if (i < garbage.length - 1) {
            time_travel[0] += travel[i];
            time_travel[1] += travel[i];
            time_travel[2] += travel[i];
        }
    }
    return time_garbage[0] + time_travel[0] + time_garbage[1] + time_travel[1] + time_garbage[2] + time_travel[2];
}
```

    This algorithm iterates through the garbage and travel arrays simultaneously. It keeps track of two sets of time counters: one for the time spent on picking up each type of garbage and one for the time spent on traveling between houses. In each iteration, it counts the number of 'M', 'P', and 'G' in a house's garbage string and adds it to the respective time_garbage counters. It also adds the travel[i] value to the respective time_travel counters for all three types of garbage. Finally, it returns the total time spent on picking up garbage and traveling for all three types.

